-- Barclays Chairman Shocked by Public Outcry, Financial Mail Says
-- B y   M a k i k o   K i t a m u r a
-- 2012-07-08T12:27:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-08/barclays-chairman-shocked-by-public-outcry-financial-mail-says.html
Barclays Plc Chairman Marcus Agius is
shocked by the public outcry over the bank’s Libor-rigging
scandal, the  Financial Mail  said, citing an interview with the
65-year-old executive.  The crisis is the worst in his experience, and the bank
will take action to regain the public’s trust, the Mail said,
citing Agius.  To contact the reporter on this story:
